<br>
<br>
Well, frankly most of the people post here (myself certainly included) have no idea what it is like soloing at 20-50 with 6 pieces of DW armor, probably 46+ total chest/leg ac, and maybe a 20/30 to 30/40 or better 2h weapon.<br>
<br>
All of that (and a FBSS) is *very* purchaseable on E'ci server from moneys made from selling monster drops to NPCs from green mobs by the mid 30's to 40's.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uruadinstoutheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ruadin Stoutheart</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.kc.rr.com/matts50l/icon.JPG" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight Of the Realm</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/16/02 2:44:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15286.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paladins Solobility-Equipment dependable?</span><hr size=1> I am 60 and I solo, but its not the greatest for me.  <br>
<br>
I still don't know how people can get 3 AA points in 6-7 hours or so of solo (as several have claimed), as I spent 10 hours (with clarity II at all times, probably % 30-40 of that with AQ) fighting undead basically non-stop and got around 1.5 points.  <br>
<br>
The only conclusion I can get is the gear differences, my gear is not that good at all (I use a Argent Protector, some Scaled Knights armor etc), I assume with a better weapon and some better armor I could get points faster.  But it seems odd that there is a %333 difference in just gear alone....<br>
<br>
If so I really need to re-think things <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><B>Baron Ruadin Stoutheart, <I>Crusader of Brell</I></B><BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=patryck>Patryck</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 180<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/16/02 6:17:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15286.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paladins Solobility-Equipment dependable?</span><hr size=1> I have soloed most of my Paladins life and must say it is fairly easy and safe. If you get in trouble use LoH, get in trouble and need to run root or ghetto fear(FoL) pretty simple. I do not have very good gear and i have done well for myself up to now. Gets a lot easier after 30 IMO. <p>Patryck                                 
Officer of Eternal Empires
Vallon Zek</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dalzielpureheart>Dalziel Pureheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/16/02 6:26:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15286.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Solo</span><hr size=1> Primal/ntoV loot is certainly not necessary to Solo. I can solo pretty well and I only have 1 piece of ToV armor. (Bracer, all other visible armor = Deepwater.) Using a massive dragonclaw shard or argent protector for solo. CC helps a LOT. Clarity also helps big time. I primarily solo in velks as its easy to solo, and if you get bored, you only have to put on your LFG tag and you can get in a group pretty easy. Im getting 1 blue an hour Solo in Velks in 59. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukilmarfyrewynd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kilmar Fyrewynd</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Holy Defender</span><br>  Posts: 686<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/16/02 6:51:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15286.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Solo</span><hr size=1> I solo fine. Check my equipment out. Nothing major.  <p><b><i><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=74373>Kilmar Fyrewynd</a><BR>
60th Crusader<BR>
<a href=http://www.farrout.net/kingscourt/>King's Court</a><BR>
Drinal Server<BR>
</b></i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubizomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bizomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fatcat </span><br>  Posts: 994<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/16/02 7:11:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15286.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Solo</span><hr size=1> Melees are gear dependant. It's always been this way. The better your gear the better your soloability. Of course how you play your character and skills can help you take on mobs others can't. But it's going to come down to gear at some point.<br>
<br>
<br>
Biz.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umarlowelawbringer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Marlowe Lawbringer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Holy Defender</span><br>  Posts: 931<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/16/02 7:19:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15286.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Solo</span><hr size=1> I've been soloing a lot in FG and my exp moves a lot slower than others here report. My gear is not so great these days, I guess; I'm using FD with a CoCW and have three pieces of Shining (BP, arms, gauntlets), Thurg quest boots, WW legs, DW helm and bracers. I don't have clarity and cast as few CCs as I can, healing with the DW helm afterwards. Although fasting than medding for heals, the downtime of healing 2-3K HPs with the helm is not inconsiderable. I did have KEI on last night, the remains of a raid I guested on the night before, and it changed my tactics completely. Even with BoT on (which I do not use when clarityless), I could cast CC, and by the time it recyled, I had regained most of the mana used. I was able to pull virtually nonstop. I cried when it faded <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Marlowe Lawbringer<BR>
Crusader of Mithaniel Marr, Level 60 <BR>Innoruuk<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukidkod1ak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kidkod1ak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 281<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/16/02 7:29:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15286.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Solo</span><hr size=1> I solo at a reasonable rate in my opinion. I usually dont bother soloing without c3 tho. Given that if I hang out in the Bazaar or Nexus until I get KEI I can then run to the Grey(skellies and Shissar) or ME(umbrous toilers, skeletal drudges, bats) and solo with little downtime. I could probably do shrooms in FG as well although that zone seems a little crowded on CT.<br>
<br>
My gear is FAR from uber. I  have no, zero, zip Scaled Knights or Shining armor. Click my profile to check my gear. <p><bold><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=101014">Varner Rapscallion</a> 
<br>Crusader for Brell
<br> Master Brewer, Fletcher, Potter, Baker
</bold>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwhitefyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whitefyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Crusader</span><br>  Posts: 245<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/16/02 8:02:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15286.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Solo</span><hr size=1> Yeah KEI is awesome for soloing. I'm not worried about exp anymore, so I usually don't bother trying to solo unless I get KEI. With it i can solo rock fiends instead of snakes and skellies. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=callalily>Callalily</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/16/02 8:25:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15286.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Solo</span><hr size=1> I soloed my old paladin quite a bit from about 30 something to 40 in Crystal Caverns when it first opened. It was a very nice little run there. I wasn't amazingly decked out, but a nice weapon did help loads. When I was finally able to drop my harpoon for a mith 2hander it became very easy to solo there.<br>
<br>
Now I'm at 23 and while I'm waiting for a group I often solo but I'm much equipped now. The arbitors has been amazing once I hit 20 and gives me plenty of time to cast between swings as well. I got it for about 500 platinum which was pretty easy for me to scrape together by 20 selling pickbringers coif's to the vendors and things like that. It's fairly easy for me to fear park undead in unrest without too much effort as long as I pull well. It get's a little iffy around 23 though. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  That stairway starts to look awfully inviting. lol.<br>
<br>
Bottom line. Yes, you can solo fairly well in your 20's and 30's. Equipment will cut your down time of course. And lack of equipment can limit the places that you can effectively solo. Make friends with enchanters if you can. Pay them a fair sum for a clarity or breeze if you come across one and she will be happy to give you another later most likely if you can come to them.<br>
<br>
Good luck to ya. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=158863">Callalily Serein</A><BR>
The Littlest Knight of Karana<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwyrmbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>wyrmbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 138<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/16/02 9:06:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15286.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/oddnfun/wyrmbane_sml.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Solo</span><hr size=1> <br>
The other paladin in my guild tends to Solo a lot.   Due to his time constraints over the past 2 months he can get online for about 2 hours maximum at a given time.<br>
<br>
In that time, he has gone from 30 to 37, occasionally getting 1 person to hunt with, but mostly hunting solo.<br>
<br>
His armor, is just Armor of Ro, I provided since it was rotting the bank, and for weapons he has a Blackened Alloy or Wurmslayer + Shield.   Currently, he does not have a haste item of any type.<br>
<br>
So, yes, it is very possible for a paladin to solo his entire career.  It is by no means fast, sometimes painful, and you have to pick the right spots so you get mobs that are blue but at the bottome of the dark blue spectrum.   <br>
<br>
wyrmbane <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaleani.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saleani</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 97<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/16/02 9:12:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15286.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Solo</span><hr size=1> Gear helps, but it is not a cure for player skill. &quot;A fool with a tool is still a fool.&quot; This game has a strong bent towards being gear dependant.<br>
<br>
I solo from time to time. To get the faction I needed for some Chardok quests, I had to hunt from 40-45 almost exclusively in FM, Droga and Nurga. Sometimes I do Kithicor at nite.<br>
<br>
My gear? Pretty nice, but I have had most of it since my low 20s.<br>
<br>
For soloing, mostly you will find that you need something to help heal a lot, DW helm works for that when you are 45+. I have a regen bp (the ceremonial iksar), and that makes a huge difference soloing also. The only items I don't have that I wish I did are &quot;flowing thought&quot; items. <br>
<br>
In short, for soloing a lot, to minimized down time, you will want some sort of hp and manna regen items. Or you will sit on your butt medding too much to have fun. <p><a href='http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=64195'>Combat Profile</a><br>
<a href='http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=64207'>Tradeskill Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showPrevMessage?topicID=15286.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showNextMessage?topicID=15286.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15286.topic&index=20><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.emailToFriend?topicID=15286.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.threadControl?topicID=15286.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=15286.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=15286.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="paladinsofnorrathgeneral">General<option value="paladinsofnorrathfrm14">Norrath Classic and Kunark<option value="paladinsofnorrathfrm15">Velious and Luclin<opti